Package: resquin
Title: provides functions to calculate common response quality indicators in survey reseach
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Matthias", "Roth", , "matthias.roth@gesis.org", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-4369-8106"))
Description: resquin (response quality indicators) provides functions to calculate common survey data quality indicators, such as response style indicators. Currently, resquin provides two functions.resp_distributions() - Calculates response quality indicators (e.g. within person mean and standard deviation over a set of survey questions). resp_styles() - Calculates response style indicators (e.g. extreme response style or middle response style).
